{
  "stem": "10588.9",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in 1978.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1978, from 1934, I have not seen my cousin Gitel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my cousin, by the time I came, the only cousin that survived on my father's side was [NON-ENGLISH], because her sister died in Israel, and my aunt died in Israel.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They died the same day, because my cousin [NON-ENGLISH] had-- I forgot how you call this kind of pregnancy, that was outside the tubes.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she didn't understand.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She didn't take care.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she died.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when they came to tell my aunt [NON-ENGLISH], she was so heart broken.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So there are two graves together.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They died same day, or it was in a day, or something like this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But anyhow when I came, that was the first time that I saw my cousin Gitel.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She found out I am there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She came.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when she met my late son, Michael, for the first time, she gave him for his bar mitzvah a tallis and a yamaka.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then she asked Michael, what would you like, something else?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, I would like a little chain with my name.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she gave him this chain that I'm wearing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It says Michael.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Michael was wearing it for many years on his neck.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then when he got older, he said, Mom, why don't you wear it for me?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I would like to have a herringbone chain, they call it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, like a bigger one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had one.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I took it off of my neck, and I gave it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he had-- it didn't take long.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I received the call from Israel that my cousin Gitel died.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She still had a chance to see me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I don't need to tell you  the reunion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And from her, I got some photographs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, unfortunately, it was 1990, in May.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was supposed to be the graduation of my son Jerry Jakov.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Was supposed to graduate from engineering school in Cornell University.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And Michael, at that time, was already graduated too, and had his own home, and did very well, both as far as liked with his friends, and had has his own home, $125,000 that he paid, a wonderful job, and was well-liked and respected.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he left on Thursday, and he said to me, Mom, Dad, please get ready, and I'm going to come and pick you up to take to the brother's graduation.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Friday, the police came in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[SOBBING] And to tell me the most horrible news.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My son Michael was killed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Michael is dead.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My cousin Gitel is dead.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I had to survive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I saw, lived through, the unspeakable horrors of the Holocaust, rise and fall of Nazi Germany, of Hitler and the Third Reich, and lived to be in Israel and still to see my cousin Gitel.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And this chain has a lot history of history.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This is the most precious piece of jewelry for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And when Michael died, he left a lot behind, a lot of love and friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The only thing he could take with him is his tallis.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And this is very precious to me because it has so much history.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So I remembered what my grandmother said, 'With God, all things are possible.'",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In a car accident.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Instantly killed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never said goodbye to my family, except for my cousin Gitel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And twice, once in 1934 and once before I left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then in 1981, I went to the world gathering.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is going to come the end of another story that we had done before.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they wanted me also to participate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They made also a little show, a documentary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nothing like this, but it was a little bit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They looked for somebody.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Everybody said, Itka, because I was speaking from the Holocaust since 1974.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I was invited to come.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was the last day of the march.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And everybody was marching to the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Menachim Begin is the prime minister.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I cannot express the emotion.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "For 2,000 years, we prayed, and here the state of Israel from the gates of Auschwitz, the gate from hell to heaven.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I couldn't march, because they wanted me to be there in case the youth have questions and everything.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I had a badge.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Everybody who came to the world gathering had a badge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And on the badge, just Itka Zygmuntowicz, USA.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Everybody's country.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We came with children, grandchildren, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went by myself that time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we came there, I was standing, and I asked somebody for a pen or a marker.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, who's going to know me?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't expect family.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But even somebody-- a friend, an acquaintance, a neighbor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So many years.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have a different name now.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
